                <li>An applicant can choose multiple categories while applying.</li>
                <li>Applicants must pay a non-refundable fee for each selected category to ensure high-quality processing.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- FAQ SECTION -->
<section class="l-section" id="faq" style="background: var(--l-accent);">
    <div class="l-container">
        <h2 class="l-section-title">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)</h2>
        <p class="l-section-sub">Certification of Environment Auditors (CEAs) through Recognition of Prior Learning (RPL)</p>
        
        <div class="l-faq-container">
            <!-- FAQ 1 -->
            <div class="l-faq-item">
                <div class="l-faq-header" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
                    <span class="l-faq-title">What is the CEA RPL certification programme?</span>
                    <i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="l-faq-icon"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="l-faq-content">
                    The CEA RPL programme is a certification pathway for experienced professionals to become Certified Environment Auditors (CEAs) through Recognition of Prior Learning (RPL), under Clause 7(i) of the Environment Audit Rules, 2025. It recognises the existing knowledge and professional experience of eligible candidates, allowing them to obtain certification without undergoing full formal training.
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- FAQ 2 -->
            <div class="l-faq-item">
                <div class="l-faq-header" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
                    <span class="l-faq-title">Who administers this certification programme?</span>
                    <i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="l-faq-icon"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="l-faq-content">
                    The programme is administered by the Environment Audit Designated Agency (EADA), under the Ministry of Environment, Forest and Climate Change (MoEF&CC).
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- FAQ 3 -->
            <div class="l-faq-item">
                <div class="l-faq-header" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
                    <span class="l-faq-title">How many categories of Environment Audits are available for certification?</span>
                    <i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="l-faq-icon"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="l-faq-content">
                    There are four categories:
                    <ul class="mt-2" style="list-style-type: none; padding-left: 0;">
                        <li>• Category 1: Compliance or Verification Audits (under EP Act, Water Act, Air Act, and related rules)</li>
                        <li>• Category 2: Verification or Assessment Audits (BRSR under SEBI LODR Regulations)</li>
                        <li>• Category 3: Compliance or Verification Audits under Forest Conservation Act</li>
                        <li>• Category 4: Compliance or Verification Audits under Wildlife Protection Act</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="mt-2">An applicant may apply for one or more categories simultaneously.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- FAQ 4 -->
            <div class="l-faq-item">
                <div class="l-faq-header" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
                    <span class="l-faq-title">Who is eligible to apply?</span>
                    <i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="l-faq-icon"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="l-faq-content">
                    An applicant must:
                    <ul class="mt-2" style="list-style-type: none; padding-left: 0;">
                        <li>• Be an Indian citizen</li>
                        <li>• Hold a Bachelor's, Master's, or Ph.D. degree from a UGC/AICTE recognised institution in a relevant discipline</li>
                        <li>• Have the requisite years of post-qualification professional experience (12 years for Bachelor's, 10 years for Master's, 8 years for Ph.D.)</li>
                        <li>• Be below 70 years of age as on the closing date of the application</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- FAQ 5 -->
            <div class="l-faq-item">
                <div class="l-faq-header" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
                    <span class="l-faq-title">What educational qualifications are required for each category?</span>
                    <i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="l-faq-icon"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="l-faq-content">
                    <strong>For Categories 1 & 2:</strong> Disciplines such as Environmental Sciences, Environmental Engineering, Civil, Chemical, Mechanical, Electrical, Industrial, Production, Metallurgical, Mining or Agricultural Engineering, Architecture, Town and Country Planning, Urban and Regional Planning, Biotechnology, Life Sciences, Earth Sciences, Marine Sciences, Oceanography, Coastal Sciences, Environmental Management, Sustainability Studies, Toxicology, Climate Science, Atmospheric Sciences, Waste Management, Renewable Energy, and related disciplines.
                    <p class="mt-2"><em>Note: Geology, Hydrology, Agricultural Sciences, Botany, and Microbiology are applicable only for Master's or Ph.D. holders.</em></p>
                    
                    <p class="mt-3"><strong>For Category 3:</strong> Forestry, Natural Resource Management, Wetland, and related disciplines.</p>
                    <p class="mt-2"><strong>For Category 4:</strong> Zoology, Botany, Wildlife Sciences, Ecology, Biodiversity, and related disciplines.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- FAQ 6 -->
            <div class="l-faq-item">
                <div class="l-faq-header" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
                    <span class="l-faq-title">What happens if my application is incomplete?</span>
                    <i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="l-faq-icon"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="l-faq-content">
                    Incomplete applications will be summarily rejected. No correspondence will be entertained in this regard. Applicants are strongly advised to ensure all required documents are uploaded and the application is complete before submission.
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- FAQ 7 -->
            <div class="l-faq-item">
                <div class="l-faq-header" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
                    <span class="l-faq-title">Is the application fee refundable?</span>
                    <i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="l-faq-icon"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="l-faq-content">
                    No. The application certification fee is mandatory and non-refundable, regardless of the outcome of the application. A separate fee is applicable for each audit category selected.
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- FAQ 8 -->
            <div class="l-faq-item">
                <div class="l-faq-header" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
                    <span class="l-faq-title">Where can I find the detailed guidelines for the CEA RPL programme?</span>
                    <i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="l-faq-icon"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="l-faq-content">
                    The detailed guidelines are available on the official websites of MoEF&CC and EADA. Applicants are advised to read the guidelines carefully before submitting their application.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- CTA FINAL -->
<section class="l-section">
    <div class="l-container">
        <div class="cta-card p-5" style="border-radius: 40px; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0ea5a5 0%, #064e4e 100%);">
            <h2 class="text-white fw-bold display-5">Begin Your Application Process</h2>
            <p class="text-white opacity-75 fs-5">Apply for Certification of Environmental Auditors through the official RPL application portal.</p>
            <button onclick="openRoleModal()" class="btn btn-light btn-lg px-5 py-3 fw-bold mt-4" style="color: #0ea5a5; border-radius: 16px;">Start Your Application</button>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- ROLE SELECTION MODAL -->
